<TITLE> Bay low likely to intensify </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 14 (bdnews24.com)The weather office Wednesday kept up local cautionary signal 3 for Cox's Bazar, Chittagong and Mongla ports as a well-marked low was brewing over the east-central Bay and adjoining area. The low was likely to intensify, the Meteorological Department said in a special weather bulletin. "Under the influence of the low, deep convection was taking place over the north Bay," the bulletin said. The maritime ports might be affected by "squally weather". All fishing boats and trawlers over the north Bay and deep sea have been advised to come close to the coast and proceed with caution until further notice. bdn
